    • Constructor Detail

      • BASS_BFX_FLANGER

        public BASS_BFX_FLANGER()
        Create an object that holds a null BASS_BFX_FLANGER.
        The call isNull() on the object created will returns true.
          BASS_BFX_FLANGER obj = new BASS_BFX_FLANGER();
  (obj == null) <=> false
  obj.isNull() <=> true
        To creates a new BASS_BFX_FLANGER, use the static "constructor" : 
          BASS_BFX_FLANGER obj = BASS_BFX_FLANGER.allocate();
        See Also:
        allocate()

    • Method Detail

      • asBASS_BFX_FLANGER

        public static BASS_BFX_FLANGER asBASS_BFX_FLANGER(Pointer pointer)
        Create a view of the Pointer object as a BASS_BFX_FLANGER object.
        This view is valid only if the memory holded by the Pointer holds a BASS_BFX_FLANGER object.

      • allocate

        public static BASS_BFX_FLANGER allocate()
        Allocate a new BASS_BFX_FLANGER.
        The call isNull() on the object created will return false.
          BASS_BFX_FLANGER obj = BASS_BFX_FLANGER.allocate();
  (obj == null) <=> obj.isNull() <=> false
